  "title": "What to say if something happens to please you or to displease you",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 218",
  "arabic": "كَانَ النَّبِيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم إِذَا أَتَاهُ الْأَمْرُ يَسُرُّهُ قَالَ الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ الَّذِي بِنِعْمَتِهِ تَتِمُّ الصَّالِحَاتُ وَإِذَا أَتَاهُ الْأَمْرُ يَكْرَهُهُ قَالَ الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ عَلَى كُلِّ حَالٍ",
  "meaning": "When something happened that pleased him, the Prophet used to say:((Alhamdu lillaahil-lathee bini'matihi tatimmuus-saalihaat)). Praise is to Allah Who by His blessings all good things are perfected. And if something happened that displeased him, he used to say:((Alhamdulillaahi 'alaa kulli haal)).Praise is to Allah in all circumstances.",
